    "121813948": {
      "title": "Bosonized Superstring Boundary States And Partition Functions",
      "abstract": "Abstract A hole in a superstring worldsheet may be represented by a boundary state which imposes the appropriate boundary conditions relating the left-and right-moving fields. The complete bosonized boundary state is constructed by factorizing the open-string partition functions in the closed-string channel. A regularization-free derivation of the boundary corrections to the closed-superstring beta functions is sketched, using the unbosonized boundary state."
    }
